          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two identical dE -E -E telescopes were",
                "used to detect 3He nuclei. Each telescope consisted",
                "of three Si detectors: one 20-micron SSD (50x50 mm2,",
                "16 strips) and two 1000- micron SSDs (61x61 mm2, 16",
                "strips). The telescopes were located 166 mm",
                "downstream from the D2 target.",
                " Tritons emitted from 7H were detected by the 64x64 mm2",
                "telescope installed at zero laboratory angle 280 mm",
                "downstream from the target. It consisted of one",
                "1500-micron Si DSD (32x32 strips) and a set of 16",
                "square CsI(Tl)/PMT modules."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Primary 11B beam was focused into a 5-mm spot on the",
                "1-mm thick beryllium production target. The secondary",
                "8He beam with energy 26 AMeV, ~90% purity, and",
                "intensity ~10**5 pps, was focused into a 17-mm spot",
                "on the deuterium gas target. The 4 mm thick gas cell",
                "was equipped with 6 mu-m stainless steel windows. The",
                "D2 target was cooled to 27 K, and its thickness made",
                "~ 3.8x10**20 cm**(-2)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
